From 631024d96893333b1bfcc6edfd253e756017b368 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Benjamin Lin <benjamin-jw.lin@mediatek.com>
Date: Tue, 2 Jun 2026 16:24:01 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] mtk: mt76: mt7996: Refactor WMM PBC to be per-band control

Problem:
Wi-Fi traffic on bands, other than 2.4GHz, is blocked.

Root Cause:
Firmware had changed WMM PBC from per-device to per-band control, but driver has not.
Hence, with new firmware, driver only configures WMM PBC on band 0 using large packet budget thresholds.
As a result, all PLE pages are reserved for band 0, and no page for other bands.
Consequently, Wi-Fi traffic on other bands is blocked.

Firmware Dependency:
Without this commit, firmware built after 2025/12/15 starts triggering this problem.

Solution:
(1) Adjust WMM PBC upper/lower boundaries.
(2) Change WMM PBC from per-device to per-band control.
(3) Handle additional event, which has same event ID but reports number of PLE pages used instead of TX packets.
(3) Add debugfs file to adjust WMM PBC upper boundaries dynamically.

Feature:
WMM
PBC (Packet Budget Control)
AC Tail Drop

Signed-off-by: Benjamin Lin <benjamin-jw.lin@mediatek.com>
